race.comment: CONCORDIA WIND (1) ran below expectations from the wide gate with a plugging sixth over 1400m at Warwick Farm. Will appreciate Grima's 3kg claim and can return to form quickly. SAVVY SPY (7) comes out of the same race as SIR LOYNE after fading late to run sixth from the outside barrier at Kembla Grange. Will roll forward again from the awkward gate but has the talent to test these. LE TROISIR (3) slashing run first-up over the unsuitable trip with a fast finishing second over 1300m at Newcastle. Showed enough in his first prep to suggest he has a future. Will benefit from the urgings of Nash Rawiller. THROTTLE RESPONSE (9) holding his form in this grade and a win looks imminent. Taken to the front with a handy second over 1550m at this track.  Sure to be thereabouts.
